# UI UX Pro Max Skill — Activation Guidelines

## When to Use This Skill

Activate the UI UX Pro Max skill (located at `~/.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/`) when the user's request involves any of the following:

### Always Activate
- Building or designing a landing page, hero section, or marketing page
- Creating a dashboard (analytics, BI, admin, sales, etc.)
- Designing a mobile app UI (React Native, Flutter, SwiftUI, Jetpack Compose)
- Generating a full-page UI component from scratch
- Requests mentioning a visual style (e.g., glassmorphism, brutalism, dark mode, claymorphism)
- Any request that names an industry + UI (e.g., "fintech app", "wellness platform", "SaaS homepage")

### Activate When Context Suggests UI/UX Work
- User says: build, design, create, implement, make, or generate + any UI noun
- User mentions a tech stack alongside a product type (e.g., "Next.js SaaS dashboard")
- User asks to "improve", "fix", or "review" an existing UI/UX
- User specifies a color scheme, font, or design mood

### Do NOT Activate
- Pure backend or API work with no UI output
- Writing tests, migrations, or scripts with no visual component
- Debugging logic errors unrelated to UI
- Documentation or README writing

## How to Invoke the Skill

1. Read `~/.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md` first for full instructions
2. For design system generation, run:

```
   python3 ~/.cursor/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/scripts/search.py "<product type>" --design-system
```

   On Windows, use `python` instead of `python3` if `python3` is not on your PATH.

3. Use the generated design system to guide all color, typography, spacing, and component decisions before writing code

## Key Outputs the Skill Provides
- Recommended UI style (from 67 styles)
- Color palette matched to the industry
- Typography pairing (Google Fonts)
- Anti-patterns to avoid for that industry
- Pre-delivery checklist (accessibility, responsiveness, hover states)
